Colombia Stocks: Bolsa de Valores, Colinversiones, Fabricato

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-05-26T21:14:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-26/colombia-stocks-bolsa-de-valores-colinversiones-fabricato.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3:59 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index rose 1.2 percent to 14,343.92, while the
Colcap Index climbed 0.9 percent to 1733.2.  Bolsa de Valores de Colombia (BVC)  SA, the operator of
the country’s main securities exchange, rose 2.8 percent to 43.5
pesos. The bourse is scheduled to start trading with Peruvian
and Chilean exchanges May 30 in  Latin America ’s first
international exchange integration.  Cia. Colombiana de Inversiones SA (COLINV CB) rose 1.9
percent to 5,050 pesos. The company acquired 6.6 billion pesos
in assets in a hydroelectric project in San Andres de Cuerquia
in Antioquia, according to a regulatory filing.  Fabricato SA (FABRI CB), Colombia’s biggest textile maker,
advanced 5.4 percent to a four-year high of 59 pesos. Investors
are speculating the company might be sold after it said it paid
down its debts under the country’s bankruptcy law to 5.6 billion
pesos ($3 million), said Juan Fernando Restrepo, head of
research at Interbolsa SA,  Colombia ’s largest brokerage.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
